title: Pro Watercross from Naples on CBS Sports Network
text:
Pro Watercross from Naples on CBS Sports Network on Sunday Daily News staff 9:43 AM, Oct 10, 2015 9:50 AM, Oct 10, 2015 top sports | other sports Scenes from the Pro Watercross Championship at Lake Victoria in Sugned Park in Naples on Sunday, Sept., 27, 2015. (J. Scott Butherus/Staff) Copyright 2015 Journal Media Group. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed. Show Caption Previous Next 
NAPLES, Fla. - CBS Sports Network will air coverage of the 2015 Pro Watercross Tour World Championship, which took place Sept. 22-27 at Sugden Regional Park in Naples, on Sunday, Oct. 11 at 9 p.m., and again on Sunday, Oct. 18 at 9 p.m. 
“CBS Sports let us know they were so pleased with the action and coverage that they decided to add the Oct. 11 air date, as well as the originally scheduled date for Oct. 18,” said Parker Medley, sports marketing coordinator at the Naples, Marco Island, Everglades Convention and Visitors Bureau. 
To find the CBS Sports Network, visit cbssportsnetwork.com/channel-finder and type in the zip code and television service provider. Copyright 2015 Journal Media Group. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.
